      "description": "1. Rahl &amp; Wyn added Conditional actions to their recipe to create or update a Salesforce case when a line in Google Sheet is created or updated\n2. They used to the Repeat action and the list data type to iterate the conditional actions through the Google Sheet, line by line\n3. They added error monitoring and handling to their recipe so they could record failed attempts and successful attempts at transferring the data from Google Sheets to Salesforce\n4. They added data transformations so they could standardize their source data to their target system\n5. They utilized Lists by Workato to accumulate two different lists and send an email report with both lists: failed attempts and successful attempts\n6. They utilized Lookup tables to standardize City Name / Postal Code mappings between Google Sheets and Salesforce\n7. They utilized Variables by Workato to tally failed attempts and successful attempts in the email report",
